Executive Profile
John K. Wulff  Independent Director, Celanese CorporationAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 4 Board Members in 4 different organizations across 9 different industries.See Board Relationships68$239,984
Background

		Mr. John K. Wulff served as the Chief Financial Officer of Union Carbide Corporation from 1995 to March 2001. Mr. Wulff served as Corporate Vice President and Principal Accounting Officer of Union Carbide Corporation from January 1989 to December 1995 and served as its Controller from July 1987 to January 1989. He served for 14 years at Union Carbide. He has board skills and qualifications in finance and accounting; governmental and regulatory; capital structure; corporate ... governance; risk management; global operations; mergers and acquisitions; and strategic planning. He also has leadership and experience in the chemical industry and provides the board with broad chemical industry experience and finance and accounting expertise. He was a Partner at KPMG and predecessor firms from April 1977 to June 1987 and predecessor firms from 1971 to 1987. He was an Audit Partner at KPMG and its predecessor firms for ten years. He served as Chairman of Hercules Incorporated from July 2003 to November 2008. He has been a Director of Atlas Air Worldwide Holdings, Inc. since May 24, 2016. He has been an Independent Director of Celanese Corporation since August 2006, Celanese Chemicals, Inc. since August 2006 and Republic Financial Corporation since April 2006. He served as an Independent Director of Fannie Mae from December 9, 2004 to September 2008. He served as Independent Director of LANXESS Solutions US Inc. since 2010 until April 21, 2017. Mr. Wulff served as an Independent Director of Moody's Corporation from April 27, 2004 to April 12, 2016. He served as a Director of Federal National Mortgage Association since December 19, 2004. He served as an Independent Director of Sunoco, Inc. from March 8, 2004 to October 5, 2012. He served as a Member of the Financial Accounting Standards Board (FASB) from July 2001 to June 2003. He became a C.P.A. in 1974 and received a Bachelor’s of Science degree in Economics from the University of Pennsylvania in 1971.Read Full Background




